    "Furthermore, the dataset was manually split to train and evaluate the model, which could induce bias.",
    "Similarly, Miele et al. (2020) employ ResNet50V2 model to identify rodent species based on molar imagery.",
    "This study classifies species such as the house mouse (Mus musculus), European wood mouse (Apodemus sylvaticus), and Cairo spiny mouse (Acomys cahirinus) based on images of their molar tooth row.",
    "The first upper molar was used to transfer the model trained on modern, genetically identified specimens to isolated fossil teeth.",
    "A pipeline based on CNNs automatically cropped the first molar from the pictures and returned a prediction regarding species identification."
